Some of us may blame Trent, as I did yesterday, for the loss ... unfair. I had a day to recover and think: Klopp should have started Mane-Firmino-Salah, that magic potion where each ingredient was essential. Firmino, even when his scoring almost disappeared, was the catalyst for Salah's magic ... as Firmino faded away from the front line, Salah's consistent scoring dried up ... Salah, I don't think is very creative or versatile ... he had a symbiotic relation with Firmino, one provided the Brazilian spark, and the other scored. Without Firmino, Salah often looked lost, superfluous, on the field. He became an ordinary player without Firmino. Klopp forgot this relation of his original front three when he opted for Diaz who lacked experience at this CL level. What surprises me most is that Klopp always valued the subtle and tangible contribution of Firmino to his offense, and defended Firmino when he was not scoring much anymore ... I think the temptation of a youthful Diaz scoring through a spectacular run was enough to override the subtleties of Firmino's play. But Firmino was the glue that connected Salah and Mane ... without Firmino, they (Salah and Mane) are two distinct, separate entities that occasionally reach out to each other. Without Firmino Liverpool lacks Brazilian magic. You can outrun everyone and possess the ball and control ... but that is all predictable ...until you create a surprise followed by a finish. This is what Liverpool lacked.

In desperation Firmino was thrown into the game late ... and Origi ... never got a chance to do his miracle...

My conclusion: Salah needs Firmino, and Salah and Mane need Firminio to connect them. Otherwise, let all three players go.

第四祖達二月受傷後,狀態沒有怎樣提升,入球也沒有.教練團要好好輔助費明奴、祖達這種優秀第二、第三前鋒.

Solution to solve this disappointment. Sell Jota and buy Sterling. Problem solved. The truth is, everything Sterling has been doing for Man City, including breaking down the door to create an easy unmissable header opportunity leading to City's first goal when the rest of the team Man City team were off and nothing worked to break down Villa because of the big occasion and pressure of having to win the last game to be Premiere league Champions, is what Liverpool needed in this final and if Liverpool had Sterling he would have done it for Liverpool and they would have won this game. He dragged England with sudden moments of magic almost singlehandedly to the Euros Final when the rest of the England team and big names were off their game and struggling to perform to their expected high level because of the pressure and he would do it for Liverpool. I say this partly because Jota has little experience in high pressure games at the highest level and in the middle of a goal drought, while assists are not a strong part of his game, left few options in the vital moment for a substitution.  Sterling is crucial for moments like this and Pep forgetting this dropped Sterling in Man City's champions league semi final against Real Madrid resulting in them getting knocked out. He made the same mistake against Villa, but realised his error before it was too late and brought Sterling on while others were nonsensically calling for Graelish who has proved and achieved little to be asked to save the day and change the game in that high pressure situation. Let's not forget, Sterling is a Liverpool player who should have been doing all he did for Man City for Liverpool, but was sold because he was being under valued by Liverpool as proved by what he has done for Man City since he left. Sterling leaving Man City would weaken Man City, taking away a player that often shows up in big moments, can change games almost singlehandedly and consistently provides good stats for a winger in goals and assists year after year as Man City struggle to hold on to him because with all their recent spending they cannot afford him. They stole him from Liverpool and it could be a great time to return the favour with Sterling at his prime with no reason to not continue getting better. Sterling being taken from Man City by Liverpool would not only weaken their biggest rival and obstacle to the title, and weaken the effectiveness of their rivals new big striker, but would also by adding all the qualities from Sterling Man City have benefited from to Liverpool make Liverpool stronger. Those who continue to credit Pep or Pep's style of play for Sterling's great contributions and magic moments claiming he could not do it elsewhere were proved wrong when he did the same for England at the Euros. On the contrary, it is the other players in Man City's team that must prove their ability to do what they do for City in another team shirt such as their international team shirts, including Debruyne. Let's hope Liverpool are wise to this great opportunity. Sterling was note voted as the PFA World Young Player of the year with Liverpool for nothing, something England's most celebrated young players rarely if ever achieve, and he has been consistent on a high level ever since. His consistent achievements in stats and on the pitch winning trophies do not lie, forget what the media and pundits say or don't say about him to deny him his applause. I still think Sterling has a special affection for Liverpool and Liverpool must make their move. Peace and love.

1- We miss chances more than any other team in the world, and that asks for other solutions: passing the ball more to get an open goal for example.
2- a lot of times we press passively. we give the illusion of pressing instead of pressing firmly. If Militao was instead of Van-Dijk In the case of their goal, for example, he would`ve burst towards Valverde directly and eliminated the danger from there, even with a foul. Van-Dijk was chill as always, Valverde had all the time and space to do whatever he desires.
3- I feel that we are less efficient when Diaz is playing. Skillful yes, but not lethal, and not crazy fast to dribble through a defender. Jota is a goal scorer, he is clever in exploiting spaces, while Firminio is a master in linking the play, he can release Salah and Mane easily. With Diaz, we lost all that. IF you notice, we scored less in the second half of the season, when Diaz started playing more often. 
4- We need depth, I hope we sign Nunez next season.
5- I hope the players keep the talk to the manager next time. Salah didn`t learn his lesson; he said similar things before in AFC and lost, then he said "we will take our revenge in the world cup qualifier", and lost, against the same team.
6-- The best defender in the league didn`t play, Matip, and that's a crime.
7- We were close this season, and that should push us more; because we won both, the UCL and the EPL after we were close the previous year. So, let's go again for the quadruple.
